# Zsh Plugin Configuration (using Zinit)
# ---------------------------------------
#
# This file lists all the Zsh plugins you want to use.
# Zinit will automatically install and load them for you.
#
# To enable a plugin, simply uncomment the line.
# To add a new one, find it on GitHub and add a `zinit light ...` line.

# --- Recommended Plugins (uncomment to enable) ---

# Enables syntax highlighting in the command line
zinit light zsh-users/zsh-syntax-highlighting

# Suggests commands as you type, based on history
# zinit light zsh-users/zsh-autosuggestions

# Adds many useful completions that are not available by default
# zinit light zsh-users/zsh-completions

# Provides a better history search (press Ctrl+R)
# zinit light "junegunn/fzf-bin" # Installs fzf binary
# zinit light "junegunn/fzf"